The paper deals with communication over a noisy channel, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). The presence of an adversary and the need for security suggest that the paper may also belong to the cryptography sub-category (cs.CR). The use of probabilistic techniques and the analysis of error probabilities suggest that the paper may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories.
